ğŸ” Authentication & Access Control

Least Privilege vs Privilege Creep

Privileged Access Management (PAM)
Controls, monitors, and rotates privileged credentials

Credential Stuffing
Uses leaked credentials across multiple services due to password reuse

Federation / SSO / OAuth / OpenID Connect
Authenticate once, access multiple services

ğŸ§¨ Common Attacks & Threats

Evil Twin (Wireless)
Fake AP with same SSID to intercept traffic

DNS Poisoning / Spoofing
Redirects traffic by corrupting DNS cache

Man-in-the-Middle (MITM)
Often enabled by ARP/DNS attacks or rogue wireless APs

Privilege Escalation
Exploiting vulnerabilities to gain higher access rights

Buffer Overflow
Overwriting memory to execute arbitrary code

